Aluminum Co of America said it isoffering to purchase any and all of its outstanding 150 mlndlrs of 12 pct sinking fund debentures of 2012.    It said it will buy back the debentures at 1,105 dlrs per1,000 dlr principal amount, plus accrued interest up to, butnot including, the day of payment.    The offer will end at 1700 EDT (2100 GMT) on June 30,unless extended. Payment will be made on July eight. Thebuyback offer will be co-managed by Merrill Lynch CapitalMarkets and Salomon Brothers Inc, Alcoa said. Reuter&#3;